Rating: 4
I made this recipe for my picky family, and we all loved it. The pork chops were great and cooked incredibly fast. First, it is important to note that this recipe calls for 1/2 inch thick pork chops. These would also be called "thin sliced" at many places. If you get thicker pork chops, you are going to want to cook them on a lower temperature for a longer time. Mine were exactly 1/2 inch thick and cooked so fast I could hardly believe it. It is also important to note that they USDA revised their recommended cooking temperature for pork this year, and now say that 145 degrees is a safe temperature. This means that there can be some pink. This does not include ground pork, but it does go for pork chops! www.fsis.usda.gov/news/NR_052411_01/index.asp Also, I didn't have any fresh bread crumbs, but Panko bread crumbs worked great. I made my own applesauce and didn't stick to the recipe in that regard, because I happen to have a method that I like. When I was kid, when my mom didn't have time to make her own applesauce, she just heated up some from the jar in the fridge, which isn't as good, but I think it is okay in a pinch. I used 3 apples for 3 people, and had just enough sauce. My family loved this recipe, and I will definitely make it again.

