The pork chops were delicious - so tender and tasty. Everyone loved them - the seasoning in the bread crumbs, just the right amount of frying, etc. The applesauce: cut apples in quarters, place in pan with a little water, skin, seeds and all. Run through a food mill when cooked. I use two or three diff. types of apples e.g., granny smith, courtland, fuji, etc. SO EASY - I MAKE THIS EVERY TIME WE HAVE PORK. I will make the pork chops forever.

